{{short description|American film and television production company}} {{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}} {{Infobox company | name = Sunday Night Productions | logo = Sunday Night Productions logo.jpg | type = [[Privately held company|Private]] | industry = [[Production company]] | founded = {{Start date and age|2013}} | founder = [[John Krasinski]]
Allyson Seeger | location_city = [[Santa Monica, California]] | location_country = U.S. | area_served = | key_people = John Krasinski (Chairman and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]]) | products = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | website = }} '''Sunday Night Productions''' is an American film and television [[production company]] founded by [[John Krasinski]] and Allyson Seeger in 2013. It is known for producing the television series ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]'', ''[[Dream Corp LLC]]'' and ''[[Jack Ryan (TV series)|Jack Ryan]]'', the [[YouTube]] streaming news show ''[[Some Good News]]'', and the feature-length films ''[[The Hollars]]'', ''[[A Quiet Place (film)|A Quiet Place]]'', and ''[[A Quiet Place Part II]]''. ==History== In 2013, John Krasinski and Allyson Seeger formed Sunday Night Productions with Krasinski's money from ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''.{{Cite web|first=Jessica|last=Booth|url=https://amp.insider.com/john-krasinski-movies-tv-shows-2018-8|title=How John Krasinski went from 'The Office' star to a Hollywood leading man|date=August 7, 2018|website=Insider.com|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In May 2014, Krasinski and Seeger produced his film ''[[The Hollars]]'',{{Cite web|last=Yamato|first=Jen|url=https://deadline.com/2014/05/john-krasinski-direct-star-hollars-anna-kendrick-richard-jenkins-margo-martindale-724599/|title=John Krasinski To Direct and Star in 'The Hollars' With Anna Kendrick, Richard Jenkins & Margo Martindale|date=May 5, 2014|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} which was acquired by [[Sony Pictures Classics]].{{Cite web|last=McNary|first=Dave|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/sundance-john-krasinski-the-hollars-sony-classics-1201692527/|title=Sundance: John Krasinski's 'The Hollars' Bought By Sony Classics|date=January 29, 2016|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In September 2014, Krasinski would produce both Shawn Wines' law student turned garbage collection comedy, as well as Josh Siegal and Dylan Morgan's workplace/family hybrid through Sunday Night for [[NBC]], but, there have been no further developments for both shows.{{Cite web|last=Fleming|first=Mike Jr.|url=https://deadline.com/2014/09/john-krasinski-comedies-nbc-838654/|title=John Krasinski Sells 2 Comedies To NBC|date=September 22, 2014|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In November 2015, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce ''[[Dream Corp, LLC]]'' with [[Stephen Merchant]] for [[Adult Swim]].{{Cite web|last=Stanhope|first=Kate|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/john-krasinski-stephen-merchant-animated-840727|title=John Krasinski, Stephen Merchant Animated Comedy Picked Up to Series at Adult Swim|date=November 7, 2015|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In September 2016, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce Alex Carter's adaptation of the ''My Bad Parent'' book and blog for Fox, but there have been no further developments since.{{Cite web|last=Wagmeister|first=Elizabeth|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/john-krasinski-my-bad-parent-alex-carter-fox-comedy-tv-show-1201869403/|title=John Krasinski Producing Family Comedy 'My Bad Parent' at Fox (Exclusive)|date=September 28, 2016|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In March 2017, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce the film ''[[A Quiet Place (film)|A Quiet Place]]'' with [[Platinum Dunes]] for [[Paramount Pictures]], with Krasinski also co-writing and directing.{{Cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/john-krasinski-emily-blunt-movie-together-quiet-place-1201909081/|title=John Krasinski to Write, Direct and Star with Emily Blunt in 'Quiet' Thriller|date=March 15, 2017|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}} ===Projects previously in and currently in development=== In 2013, Krasinski sold a spec script to produce an action-adventure movie he wrote with Oren Uziel for [[Warner Bros]].{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|url=https://deadline.com/2013/12/john-krasinski-oren-uziel-sell-spec-to-warner-bros-ben-affleck-matt-damon-producing-653398/|title=John Krasinski, Oren Uziel Sell Spec To Warner Bros; Ben Affleck, Matt Damon Producing|date=December 16, 2013|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In April 2018, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce the sci-fi thriller ''Life on Mars'', based on a short story by Cecil Castellucci for Paramount.{{Cite web|first=Borys|last=Kit|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/john-krasinski-plans-sci-fi-thriller-life-mars-quiet-place-team-1101825?|title=John Krasinski Plans Sci-Fi Thriller 'Life on Mars' With 'A Quiet Place' Team (Exclusive)|date=April 21, 2018|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In May 2018, Sunday Night will produce Krasinski and [[Aaron Sorkin]]’s Chateut Marmont miniseries ''The Hotel on Sunset'', for [[HBO]].{{Cite web|first=Atonia|last=Blyth|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/john-krasinski-aaron-sorkin-chateau-marmont-project-1202384765/|title=John Krasinski & Aaron Sorkin Chateau Marmont Project in the Works|date=May 8, 2018|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In July 2018, Sunday Night will co-produce a [[Marc Rich]] biopic with [[Matt Damon]] in talks to play Rich.{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/matt-damon-marc-rich-bill-clinton-pardon-movie-the-king-of-oil-john-krasinski-tap-universal-1202420589/|title=Matt Damon & John Krasinski Tap into Bill Clinton-Pardoned Fugitive Marc Rich Tale 'The King of Oil' At Universal|date=July 2, 2018|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} On March 22, 2019, Sunday Night will produce the film adaptation of [[Rebecca Alexander]]’s memoir ''Not Fade Away'' for [[Annapurna Pictures]] along with [[David O. Russell]], with [[Emily Blunt]] in talks to play Alexander.{{Cite web|first=Amanda|last=N’Duka|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/emily-blunt-not-fade-away-annapurna-john-krasinski-david-o-russell-producing-1202567537/|title=Emily Blunt in Talks To Star 'Not Fade Away' At Annapurna; John Krasinski & David O. Russell Producing|date=March 21, 2019|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}} In November 2020, Krasinski will produce ''[[A Quiet Place: Day One]]'' that [[Jeff Nichols]] will write.{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|title='A Quiet Place' Spinoff in the Works With Jeff Nichols Writing, Directing|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/a-quiet-place-spinoff-in-the-works-with-jeff-nichols-writing-directing-4090164/|date=November 9, 2020|publisher=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 11, 2021}} In March 2021, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce Natalie Erika James' psychological thriller ''Apartment 7A'', for [[Paramount Players]].{{Cite web|first=Justin|last=Kroll|title=Natalie Erika James To Direct Thriller 'Apartment 7A' For Paramount Players, Sunday Night Productions And Platinum Dunes|url=https://deadline.com/2021/03/natalie-erika-james-apartment-7a-paramount-sunday-night-productions-and-platinum-dunes-1234717447/|date=March 18, 2021|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}} More recently, the company signed a first look deal with Paramount.{{Cite web|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|date=2021-05-11|title=John Krasinski Inks First-Look Deal With Paramount|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/john-krasinski-paramount-ryan-reynolds-1234951191/|access-date=2021-05-13|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en-US}} ==Filmography== ===Films=== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! contentMetadata.text: Sunday Night Productions is an American film and television production company founded by John Krasinski and Allyson Seeger in 2013. It is known for producing the television series Lip Sync Battle, Dream Corp LLC and Jack Ryan, the YouTube streaming news show Some Good News, and the feature-length films The Hollars, A Quiet Place, and A Quiet Place Part II. In 2013, John Krasinski and Allyson Seeger formed Sunday Night Productions with Krasinski's money from The Office. In May 2014, Krasinski and Seeger produced his film The Hollars, which was acquired by Sony Pictures Classics. In September 2014, Krasinski would produce both Shawn Wines' law student turned garbage collection comedy, as well as Josh Siegal and Dylan Morgan's workplace/family hybrid through Sunday Night for NBC, but, there have been no further developments for both shows. In November 2015, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce Dream Corp, LLC with Stephen Merchant for Adult Swim. In September 2016, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce Alex Carter's adaptation of the My Bad Parent book and blog for Fox, but there have been no further developments since. In March 2017, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce the film A Quiet Place with Platinum Dunes for Paramount Pictures, with Krasinski also co-writing and directing. In 2013, Krasinski sold a spec script to produce an action-adventure movie he wrote with Oren Uziel for Warner Bros. In April 2018, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce the sci-fi thriller Life on Mars, based on a short story by Cecil Castellucci for Paramount. In May 2018, Sunday Night will produce Krasinski and Aaron Sorkin’s Chateut Marmont miniseries The Hotel on Sunset, for HBO. In July 2018, Sunday Night will co-produce a Marc Rich biopic with Matt Damon in talks to play Rich. On March 22, 2019, Sunday Night will produce the film adaptation of Rebecca Alexander’s memoir Not Fade Away for Annapurna Pictures along with David O. Russell, with Emily Blunt in talks to play Alexander. In November 2020, Krasinski will produce A Quiet Place: Day One that Jeff Nichols will write. In March 2021, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce Natalie Erika James' psychological thriller Apartment 7A, for Paramount Players. More recently, the company signed a first look deal with Paramount. Allyson Seeger | location_city = [[Santa Monica, California]] | location_country = U.S. | area_served = | key_people = John Krasinski (Chairman and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]]) | products = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | website = }} Sunday Night Productions is an American film and television [[production company]] founded by [[John Krasinski]] and Allyson Seeger in 2013. It is known for producing the television series [[Lip Sync Battle]], [[Dream Corp LLC]] and [[Jack Ryan (TV series)|Jack Ryan]], the [[YouTube]] streaming news show [[Some Good News]], and the feature-length films [[The Hollars]], [[A Quiet Place (film)|A Quiet Place]], and [[A Quiet Place Part II]].

texts.title: History
texts.value: In 2013, John Krasinski and Allyson Seeger formed Sunday Night Productions with Krasinski's money from [[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jessica|last=Booth|url=https://amp.insider.com/john-krasinski-movies-tv-shows-2018-8|title=How John Krasinski went from 'The Office' star to a Hollywood leading man|date=August 7, 2018|website=Insider.com|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In May 2014, Krasinski and Seeger produced his film [[The Hollars]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=Yamato|first=Jen|url=https://deadline.com/2014/05/john-krasinski-direct-star-hollars-anna-kendrick-richard-jenkins-margo-martindale-724599/|title=John Krasinski To Direct and Star in 'The Hollars' With Anna Kendrick, Richard Jenkins & Margo Martindale|date=May 5, 2014|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> which was acquired by [[Sony Pictures Classics]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=McNary|first=Dave|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/sundance-john-krasinski-the-hollars-sony-classics-1201692527/|title=Sundance: John Krasinski's 'The Hollars' Bought By Sony Classics|date=January 29, 2016|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In September 2014, Krasinski would produce both Shawn Wines' law student turned garbage collection comedy, as well as Josh Siegal and Dylan Morgan's workplace/family hybrid through Sunday Night for [[NBC]], but, there have been no further developments for both shows.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Fleming|first=Mike Jr.|url=https://deadline.com/2014/09/john-krasinski-comedies-nbc-838654/|title=John Krasinski Sells 2 Comedies To NBC|date=September 22, 2014|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In November 2015, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce [[Dream Corp, LLC]] with [[Stephen Merchant]] for [[Adult Swim]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Stanhope|first=Kate|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/john-krasinski-stephen-merchant-animated-840727|title=John Krasinski, Stephen Merchant Animated Comedy Picked Up to Series at Adult Swim|date=November 7, 2015|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In September 2016, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce Alex Carter's adaptation of the My Bad Parent book and blog for Fox, but there have been no further developments since.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Wagmeister|first=Elizabeth|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/john-krasinski-my-bad-parent-alex-carter-fox-comedy-tv-show-1201869403/|title=John Krasinski Producing Family Comedy 'My Bad Parent' at Fox (Exclusive)|date=September 28, 2016|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In March 2017, it was announced that Krasinski and Seeger will co-produce the film [[A Quiet Place (film)|A Quiet Place]] with [[Platinum Dunes]] for [[Paramount Pictures]], with Krasinski also co-writing and directing.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/john-krasinski-emily-blunt-movie-together-quiet-place-1201909081/|title=John Krasinski to Write, Direct and Star with Emily Blunt in 'Quiet' Thriller|date=March 15, 2017|website=Variety|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref>

texts.title: Projects previously in and currently in development
texts.value: In 2013, Krasinski sold a spec script to produce an action-adventure movie he wrote with Oren Uziel for [[Warner Bros]].<ref name="adventure">{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|url=https://deadline.com/2013/12/john-krasinski-oren-uziel-sell-spec-to-warner-bros-ben-affleck-matt-damon-producing-653398/|title=John Krasinski, Oren Uziel Sell Spec To Warner Bros; Ben Affleck, Matt Damon Producing|date=December 16, 2013|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In April 2018, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce the sci-fi thriller Life on Mars, based on a short story by Cecil Castellucci for Paramount.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Borys|last=Kit|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/john-krasinski-plans-sci-fi-thriller-life-mars-quiet-place-team-1101825?|title=John Krasinski Plans Sci-Fi Thriller 'Life on Mars' With 'A Quiet Place' Team (Exclusive)|date=April 21, 2018|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In May 2018, Sunday Night will produce Krasinski and [[Aaron Sorkin]]’s Chateut Marmont miniseries The Hotel on Sunset, for [[HBO]].<ref name="Marmont">{{Cite web|first=Atonia|last=Blyth|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/john-krasinski-aaron-sorkin-chateau-marmont-project-1202384765/|title=John Krasinski & Aaron Sorkin Chateau Marmont Project in the Works|date=May 8, 2018|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In July 2018, Sunday Night will co-produce a [[Marc Rich]] biopic with [[Matt Damon]] in talks to play Rich.<ref name="OilKing">{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/matt-damon-marc-rich-bill-clinton-pardon-movie-the-king-of-oil-john-krasinski-tap-universal-1202420589/|title=Matt Damon & John Krasinski Tap into Bill Clinton-Pardoned Fugitive Marc Rich Tale 'The King of Oil' At Universal|date=July 2, 2018|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> On March 22, 2019, Sunday Night will produce the film adaptation of [[Rebecca Alexander]]’s memoir Not Fade Away for [[Annapurna Pictures]] along with [[David O. Russell]], with [[Emily Blunt]] in talks to play Alexander.<ref name="Annapurna">{{Cite web|first=Amanda|last=N’Duka|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/emily-blunt-not-fade-away-annapurna-john-krasinski-david-o-russell-producing-1202567537/|title=Emily Blunt in Talks To Star 'Not Fade Away' At Annapurna; John Krasinski & David O. Russell Producing|date=March 21, 2019|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> In November 2020, Krasinski will produce [[A Quiet Place: Day One]] that [[Jeff Nichols]] will write.<ref name="QPFranchise">{{Cite web|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|title='A Quiet Place' Spinoff in the Works With Jeff Nichols Writing, Directing|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/a-quiet-place-spinoff-in-the-works-with-jeff-nichols-writing-directing-4090164/|date=November 9, 2020|publisher=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 11, 2021}}</ref> In March 2021, Krasinski and Platinum Dunes will produce Natalie Erika James' psychological thriller Apartment 7A, for [[Paramount Players]].<ref name="Apartment 7A">{{Cite web|first=Justin|last=Kroll|title=Natalie Erika James To Direct Thriller 'Apartment 7A' For Paramount Players, Sunday Night Productions And Platinum Dunes|url=https://deadline.com/2021/03/natalie-erika-james-apartment-7a-paramount-sunday-night-productions-and-platinum-dunes-1234717447/|date=March 18, 2021|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=May 22, 2019}}</ref> More recently, the company signed a first look deal with Paramount.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|date=2021-05-11|title=John Krasinski Inks First-Look Deal With Paramount|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/john-krasinski-paramount-ryan-reynolds-1234951191/|access-date=2021-05-13|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en-US}}</ref>
